        <updateDate>2022-07-20T21:07:46Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Inflation Prevention Act</b></p> <p>This bill establishes a point of order that, when the annualized rate of inflation exceeds 4.5%, prohibits the Senate from considering legislation that provides new budget authority and is estimated to result in an increase to the rate of inflation. The prohibition may be waived by an affirmative vote of three-fifths of the Senate.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
